episodes.title: Kaya o mamore! Usoppu kaizokudan daikatsuyaku!
episodes.plot: As the fight between Luffy and Kuro is close to an end, the Usopp Pirates do their best to avoid Jango.

episodes.title: Ikari bakuhatsu! Kuro vs Rufi kecchaku no yukue!
episodes.plot: Kuro's ultimate attack destroys everything in the area and Luffy becomes enraged by his lack of regard for his crew.

episodes.title: Anta ga chunjuu! Gaimon to kimyou na nakama
episodes.plot: With Usopp now in the crew and a new ship, the Going Merry, the Straw Hats head to an island said to hold a fabled treasure, only to encounter a strange man stuck in a treasure box.

episodes.title: Santouryuu no kako! Zoro to Kuina no chikai!
episodes.plot: While Usopp and Luffy fool around with the ship's cannon one day, Zoro dreams about his childhood and the promise he made to Kuina.

episodes.title: Meibutsu kokku! Kaijou resutoran no Sanji
episodes.plot: The crew meets Johnny and Yosaku, Zoro's former companions, and they set sail for the Baratie restaurant in search of a cook.

episodes.title: Manukarezaru kyaku! Sanji no meshi to Gin on
episodes.plot: Zoro, Nami, and Usopp went into the restaurant to see what's taking Luffy so long. Only to find an aftermath of a brutal fight. Sanji, who gave Iron Fist a real good kick. Is holding him with his grasp. And tells him that money won't repay the hard work he's put himself through in making that soup. Patty, a buff cook came out from the men's room saw what Sanji is doing and tries to stop him. Then Zeff and Luffy came falling through the ceiling and landed on the floor. Zeff sorted this out, as Sanji's had a long history in fighting with costumers who criticize his ...

episodes.title: Saikyou no kaizoku kantai! Teitoku Don Kurîku
episodes.plot: Gin returns to the Baratie with his also-starving captain, Don Krieg, to whom Sanji once more gives food, but Don Krieg betrays the cook once he regains his energy.

episodes.title: Mamore Baratie! Daikaizoku akaashi no Zefu
episodes.plot: It is revealed that Chef Zeff was a great pirate known as Red Leg Zeff. Gin explains the catastrophe the fleet met in Grand Line when they encountered Hawk-Eyes Mihawk, and Krieg attempts to take control of the Baratie.

episodes.title: Tama no me no Mihôku! Kenzoku Zoro umi ni chiru
episodes.plot: As Nami steals the Going Merry, Mihawk has returned to finish the job, but Zoro challenges him to a duel in order to achieve his dream.

episodes.title: Hissatsu ashiwaza sakuretsu! Sanji vs Teppeki no Pâru
episodes.plot: Mihawk leaves after defeating Zoro, so Krieg continues his invasion as Sanji reveals his fighting skills. Meanwhile, Johnny and Yosaku leave with Usopp and the wounded Zoro to go after Nami.

episodes.title: Zefu to Sanji no yume Maboroshi no ôru burû
episodes.plot: With Zeff held captive by Gin, Sanji has no choice but to take Pearl's hits, and he reflects on why Zeff means so much to him.

episodes.title: Reitetsu hijou no kijin Kaizoku kantai soutaichou Gin
episodes.plot: Gin finishes off Pearl, claiming that he wants to kill Sanji himself. Still wounded, Sanji faces Gin while Luffy attacks Don Krieg.

episodes.title: Shinaneeyo! Gekitou Rufi vs Kurîku!
episodes.plot: When Gin refuses to kill Sanji, Krieg uses poison gas on him. Luffy seems to have the advantage in the fight until Krieg pulls out his explosive Battle Spear.

episodes.title: Shitou no Ketchaku! Hara ni Kukutta Ippon no Yari!
episodes.plot: Even after taking several hits from the Battle Spear, Luffy refuses to give up.

episodes.title: Tabidachi! Umi no kokku wa Rufi to tomoni
episodes.plot: Gin decides to go back to the Grand Line with Krieg despite still being poisoned, and Sanji makes the difficult decision on whether to stay or to go with Luffy just as Yosaku comes back with the news that he knows where Nami is.

episodes.title: Higashi no Umi Saiaku no Otoko! Gyojin Kaizoku Arlong!
episodes.plot: The crew chases after Nami, who stole their ship, and Yosaku takes time during the trip to explain about Arlong and his Fishmen to Luffy and Sanji. Meanwhile, Usopp, Johnny, and Zoro arrive at the island Nami docked at.

episodes.title: Cocoyashi Mura no Majo! Arlong no Onna Kanbu
episodes.plot: Zoro is tied up by wrist to ankle. Arlong keeps asking him on what is his true plan. And Zoro kept telling him he's looking for a woman and called him half fish. Arlong let the insult went by and told Zoro that he hates man kind so much. He believes that mermen should be the superior species on the planet. As mermen are stronger and have the ability to live underwater as well as land. He's taken over the entire island he owns, and is powerful with the money he's inherited from the marines and villagers. Then a woman came out and criticize Arlong's monologuing on his ...

episodes.title: Joukinkubi! Mugiwara no Luffy Yo ni Shirewataru
episodes.plot: With Buggy, Krieg and Arlong defeated, Luffy now has the highest bounty in East Blue.

episodes.title: Honoo no Ryouri Battle? Sanji VS Bijin Chef
episodes.plot: Sanji enters a cooking contest against a woman named Carmen for an Elephant Tuna that he has always dreamed of cooking. Meanwhile Buggy and Alvida reveal themselves to Luffy who is about to be executed by them.

episodes.title: Buggy no Revenge! Shokeidai de Warau Otoko!
episodes.plot: All seems lost when Buggy has Luffy trapped on top of Gold Roger's execution platform. Can Luffy be able to escape his own death? Meanwhile an unusual storm of any king has formed up in LogueTown, and a mysterious figure appears out of no where.

episodes.title: Densetsu wa Hajimatta! Mezase Grand Line
episodes.plot: After Luffy escaped his execution, he, Zoro, and Sanji are heading back to the harbor. The storm that just occurred is like no other. But it will give the Straw Hat Pirates the advantage to use the ocean's current to head straight to the Grand Line. Meanwhile Cabaji, Buggy, and Alvida fight their way through the line of marines. They decide to retreat, so Buggy uses his special Baka Baka Car move while Alvida uses her Zero Fricition sliding move to make a get away. But Smoker used his devil's fruit power to stop them all, so that way the marines can use their own ...

episodes.title: Ikari no Kecchaku! Red Line o Norikoero!
episodes.plot: Erik the Whirlwind is still around, and would of drown if the the ocean level didn't drain. He still has the idea that the Ryuukotsu has the elixir of life. Nami corrected him, that the Ryuukotsu is calcified and is merely impossible to create elixir out of. Erik however has his eyes set on the living dragons. Instead of killing them, he offer them all a deal in sharing the Ryuukotsu. Luffy wasn't interested in the offer. Which made Erik think that Luffy isn't seeing this through. Then he finally sees it's useless to convince them that getting eternal life is good. So...

episodes.title: Kaizoku Kangei no Machi? Whiskey Peak Jouriku
episodes.plot: As the Going Merry travels to Whiskey Peak, our friends experience the Grand Line's unpredictable weather. First it was snowing, which Luffy and Usopp found an activity to do including snow ball fights and snowman building. Mr. 9 and Miss Wednesday were complaining that there's no heater. Nami told them to shut up as she couldn't help but how strange that it became cold from warm in minutes. But then she found out that they're off course according to the log pose, and need to turn 180 degrees. As everyone got busy in getting the ship back on course, they face a series...

episodes.title: Sakuretsu Santouryuu! Zoro VS Baroque Works!
episodes.plot: Zoro knows about the Baroque Works organization. And for that he must die. But he disappear off the roof. And reappeared in the crowd of bounty hunters. They got out their guns to shoot him, but they all missed and shoot each other. Mr. 8 discovers that Zoro is no ordinary swordsman. As Zoro drew his sword behind Mr. 8 before he could blink. Soon Zoro is chased by the Whiskey Peak civilians, and decides to try out the swords he got from Loguetown. And they all didn't stand a chance against Zoro's sword techniques and stealth moves. Usopp, Sanji, and Luffy were still ...

episodes.title: Shinken Shoubu! Luffy VS Zoro Nazo no Daikettou!
episodes.plot: Mr. 5 and Miss Valentine were informed by the boss that one of their agents knows some secrets that can't be leaked out. They know Mr. 8 and Miss Wednesday's true identities are were placed orders to eliminate them. Mr. 8 tries to kill them with his canons. But discovers that there's not a scratch on them. Igaram tried all he could to stop them but got hurt badly. And told Miss Wednesday(Princess Vivi) to run for it. She didn't want to leave Igaram like this. But he didn't want her to worry about him. Just remain alive for the sake of their kingdom. Mr. 9 battles Mr. ...

episodes.title: Oujo Vivi o Todokero! Luffy Kaizoku Dan Shukkou
episodes.plot: Luffy and Zoro defeated Miss Valentine and Mr. 5 while they fight their pointless battle. Nami came by and put an end to it. Luffy soon learned what really happened and forgive Zoro for thinking he killed the locals for nothing. Nami tells Vivi that they'll do it only for a matter of money. Vivi however doesn't have anything in return, she just wants to be returned to her home land safely. Nami didn't get why a princess wouldn't have any money. Vivi explained that her kingdom was wealthy long ago. Right until it got into a civil war. Which was caused by the Baroque ...

episodes.title: Unaru Netsukyuu Goukyuu! Kaizoku Dodgeball!
episodes.plot: The Davy Back Fight has just finish and Foxy is already asking for a rematch. Hit and Dead Ball game begins and the Straw Hat Crew must avoid all the tricky rules.

episodes.title: Dangai no Kessen! Daruma-san ga Koronda!
episodes.plot: The rematch begins and the Straw Hat Team is in trouble when the Hit and Dead Ball game is lost. Hopes are hanging upon the second game, DTD, where teams must rush to touch old Oni. The outcome is unexpected.

episodes.title: Captain Taiketsu! Saishuusen Combat!
episodes.plot: After losing two nakamas, Nami doubles the bet and the last round of the Davy Back fight starts. Luffy and Foxy battle in the Sexy Foxy ship, where the evil Foxy's beams are putting Luffy in a hurry.

episodes.title: Zenkai Noro Noro Kougeki VS Fujimi no Luffy
episodes.plot: Foxy carries Luffy into his ship where he has the advantage. Several rooms with dangerous weapons are waiting for him, and the Noro Noro beam keeps our hero frozen.

episodes.title: Souzetsu Nettou Combat! Unmei no Saishuu Kecchaku
episodes.plot: Luffy defeats Foxy using a piece of mirror that got stuck in his afro and wins the Davy Back Fight. 500 nakamas come into his crew among which he gets Robin and Chopper back. Old Oni meets his grandson the digger.

episodes.title: Ushinatta? Ubawareta? Omae wa Dare Da?
episodes.plot: After leaving Long Ring Long Land the crew drops the anchor in an unknown island to spend the night. They are visited by a mysterious Fishwoman who plays a song, and everybody wakes up without their memories, except Robin.

episodes.title: Fue o Idaita Nazo no Shounen to Robin no Suiri!
episodes.plot: Robin is the only one who has her memories untouched and she must keep the crew together. Nami and Zoro leave on their own but the archaeologist manages to convince the rest. The mysterious guilty boy appears.

episodes.title: Iza Kioku o Dakkan Seyo! Kaizoku Dan Shima ni Jouriku
episodes.plot: Luffy and his crew confronts the Mysterious Boy but he escapes after giving Luffy's memories back. The crew goes after his lost friends but the Boy has some plans for Zoro. Robin begins to unravel the mystery.

episodes.title: Kiba o Muku Zoro! Tachihadakatta Yajuu!
episodes.plot: Robin discovers the secret of the memories-eating monster and goes after him with Sanji, Chopper, Usopp, Luffy and Nami, whose gold Sanji is carrying. Zoro comes looking for Luffy and the battle begins.

episodes.title: Honjou o Awarashita Kioku Dorobou no Saigo Gyakushuu
episodes.plot: The Seahorse and the boy confront the crew but Sanji kick's the boy's ass just when he is trying to attack Nami and Usopp. Memories come back and the battle begins. Luffy is the only one who can fight without memories.

episodes.title: Hokori takaki otoko! Gin Gitsune no Foxy
episodes.plot: The Straw Hat Crew find Foxy in the sea and help him get to his ship. Luffy fights against the pirates that are trying to steal the Sexy Foxy and defeats them, just to discover that Foxy has been planning treason.

episodes.title: Mottomo Muteki ni Tsuyoi Yatsu? Tomottomo Kiken na Otoko!
episodes.plot: After being defeated again, Foxy keeps trying to disturb and the crew surprises him using a crab robot. Luffy and friends land in a new island where they find a powerful marine leader, Aokiji.

episodes.title: Kaigun Honbu Taishou Aokiji! Saikou Senryoku no Kyoui
episodes.plot: Aokiji says to be in the island just to locate the whereabouts of Robin, and both he and the crew help the shipwreck survivors to leave the island. But then the Admiral decides to fight and he attacks Nico.

episodes.title: Gomu to Koori no Ikkiuchi! Luffy vs Aokiji
episodes.plot: Luffy tells the crew to protect Robin and leave him alone with Aokiji. Ice and Rubber face each other but the Straw Hat captain is defeated. Sanji and Zoro save him and the Going Merry continues it's voyage.

episodes.title: Shissou Umi Ressha to Mizu no Toshi Water Seven
episodes.plot: The Straw Hat Crew arrives to a Blue Station where they meet the great Sea Train. Old guard Kokoro tells them about Water 7 and they sail to the island looking for a carpenter to repair the Going Merry.

episodes.title: Suijou Toshi no Bouken! Mokushise Kyodai Zousen Koujou
episodes.plot: Luffy, Nami and Usopp go with the gold looking for exchange and the shipyards where they can repair their ship. Chopper finally finds a library but Robin disappears. Zoro receives some visits in the Going Merry.

episodes.title: Franky ikka to Iceberg san!
episodes.plot: Zoro gets rid of the Franky Family, while Sanji gets lost in the city and watches Robin disappear with a masked man. Luffy, Nami and Usopp meet carpenter Kaku and Mayor Iceberg. The Franky Family steals their money.

episodes.title: Garera Company! Soukan Ichiban Dock
episodes.plot: The Franky Family is still after the money while Zoro talks with Kaku about the Going Merry. When Kaku returns to the shipyard with the terrible news, Luffy and Nami realizes that Usopp is gone.

episodes.title: Kaizoku Yuukai Jiken to Shi o Matsu Dake no Kaizokusen
episodes.plot: Usopp is kidnapped by the Franky Family. Nami and Luffy realize and Luffy goes after him. The rest of the crew is receiving the new about Merry. Usopp confront the burglars at the Franky House.

episodes.title: Nakama Kyuushutsu! Harikomi Franky House
episodes.plot: The Straw Hat Crew arrives to the Franky House looking for their friend and they easily beat the Franky Famlily, but their boss has already escaped with the money. Chopper heal Usopp while Luffy makes a decision.

episodes.title: Gekka no Oogenka! Kanashimi ni Hirugaeru Kaizokuki!
episodes.plot: Usopp is healed by Chopper and he asks for the Going Merry's future. A worrying quarrel begins when Luffy tells him his decision. He and Usopp argue until the Lier leaves the ship and asks Luffy for a duel.

episodes.title: Luffy VS Usopp! Butsukaru Otoko no Iji
episodes.plot: The most terrible fight begins and Usopp has prepared some tricks to fool Luffy, but the strength of the captain is clear. Memories go back and forth while even Merry is crying.

episodes.title: Genkishin Mizu no Toshi! Nerawareta Iceberg
episodes.plot: The crew has moved to a hotel when Nami arrives with the news about Iceburg. She and Luffy go to find out more while Sanji and Chopper keep tracing Robin. In dock 1, Franki appears looking for Luffy.

episodes.title: Gomu Gomu Ningen VS Ka o Fuku Cyborg
episodes.plot: Franky wants to fight Luffy but in the meantime Iceburg awakes and tell the carpenters what he saw. The Galle-La five go after Luffy and they interrupt the fight. Aqua Laguna is coming.

episodes.title: Hannin wa Mugiwara Kaizukudan? Mizu no Toshi Youjinbou
episodes.plot: Franky interferes in the battle and Nami and Luffy escape. The city is looking for the Straw Hat Pirates when Luffy rushes into Iceburg's residence, trying to find the truth. Iceburg confirms Robin's guilt.

episodes.title: Eien no Wakare? Yamo o Hiku Onna Nico Robin
episodes.plot: The crew is spread throughout the city, Sanji and Chopper go back to the ship to warn Usopp about the Aqua Laguna. Chopper smells Robin and she declares her farewell.

episodes.title: Robin o Tsukamaero! Mugiwara Ichimi no Ketsui
episodes.plot: The crew decides to go after Robin and determine once and for all whether she is their nakama or not. People of Water 7 gather in Iceburg's residence to protect him during the arrival of Aqua Laguna.

episodes.title: Aizu wa Hougeki to Tomoni! Ugokidashita CP9
episodes.plot: Night has fallen and the Galley-La soldiers are waiting. CP9 spies appear while the Straw Hat Crew is patiently waiting hidden in a tree. Iceburg tries to protect his treasure, but it's too late. Battle has began.

episodes.title: Kamen o Totta CP9! Sono Odoroki no Sugao
episodes.plot: Luffy decides to start moving but he gets stuck between two buildings. The rest of the crew makes it to the back garden where they are forced to beat the shipwrights. CP9's identities are unmasked in front of Iceburg's eyes.

episodes.title: Himeta Kizuna! Iceberg to Franky
episodes.plot: CP9 members untangle Iceburg's plan to maintain Pluton's whereabouts in secret and decide to go after Franky. Meanwhile, both Luffy and Pauly, and Nami, Zoro and Chopper arrive to Iceburg's room.

episodes.title: Kaete Koi Robin! CP9 to no Taiketsu!
episodes.plot: The CP9 members show their true strength when the Straw Hat Pirates decide to attack. Either Luffy nor Zoro manage to beat them. There are 2 minutes left for the huge fire and Robin escapes once again.

episodes.title: Mugiwara Kaizoku Dan Zenmetsu? Model Leopard no Kyoui
episodes.plot: The Galley-La company main building is set on fire and the CP9 members go after Franky, who is trying to make friends with Usopp. Aqua Laguna has arrived and both Luffy and Zoro have been thrown to the water.

episodes.title: Fune kara mo Aisareta Otoko! Usopp no Namida!
episodes.plot: Franky shows Usopp how inevitable the perish of the Going Merry is and the mysteries about the man who repaired the ship in Skypeia are revealed. The CP9 agents arrive to Franky's hidden warehouse.

episodes.title: Franky no Kako! Umi ressha ga Hashitta Hi
episodes.plot: CP9 agents discover an antique room in the warehouse. Memories awake while Franky tries to stop them before everything is destroyed: Tom's prosecution and the Umi Ressha's first trip.

episodes.title: Spandum no Inbou! Umi Ressha ga Yureta Hi
episodes.plot: Goverment CP5 agent Spandam frames Tom so he can freely investigate him and find Pluton's blueprints. The Fishman hands the plans to his apprentices and the beginning of Iceburg and Franky's enmity is revealed.

episodes.title: Densetsu no Otoko no Saigo! Umi Ressha ga Naita Hi
episodes.plot: Tom decides not to fight against the government and accepts to go to Eines Lobby in exchange of the exoneration of Iceburg and Franky. Franky can't bear the guilt and attacks Spandam, who is now CP9 boss.

episodes.title: Uragiri no Shinsou! Robin no Kanashiki Ketsui!
episodes.plot: The CP9 agents take Frany and Usopp and prepare the last-minute departure of the Umi Ressha. Meanwhile, Chopper rescues Pauly and Iceburg, who tells Nami the truth about Robin. Sanji's plan comes into action.

episodes.title: Nakama o Hikihanasu Kiteki! Hashiridasu Umi Ressha
episodes.plot: Chopper goes to search the city looking for Luffy and Zoro while Nami rushes to the train station. The Umi Ressha departs earlier than expected due to the Aqua Laguna and Sanji decides to sneak in.

episodes.title: Sanji Totsunyuu! Arashi no Naka no Umiressha Battle!
episodes.plot: Sanji is spotted by the agents in the last wagon and forced to fight. The Aqua Laguna is arriving and Pauly prevents Nami from drowning. She goes looking for Luffy and find him stuck between two walls.
